<h3>Getting here by car</h3>

<p>
    <strong>Please note that there is no parking available on site</strong>, however there limited is on-street pay and display parking on West Road and the surrounding streets.
    There are also several <a href="https://www.cambridge.gov.uk/car-parks-map">car parks in the city centre</a> within walking distance of the venue. Alternatively, parking is
    available at <a href="http://www.cambridgeshire.gov.uk/info/20149/park_and_ride/556/park_and_ride">Madingley Road Park and Ride</a> site, with a bus towards Cambridge.
    You will need to get off the bus at the Bridge Street stop and <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/14vHw">walk to the venue</a> (approx. 15 mins).
</p>

<br />
<h3>Getting here by train</h3>

<p>
    Cambridge railway station is located a few miles away from the venue. Buses can be caught outside the station to the city centre (take the
    <a href="http://www.stagecoachbus.com/PdfUploads/Timetable_42102_%20Cambridge%20citi%201.pdf">Citi 1</a> towards Arbury,
    <a href="http://www.stagecoachbus.com/PdfUploads/Timetable_45728_%20Cambridge%20citi%203.pdf">Citi 3</a> towards Fison Road,
    <a href="http://www.stagecoachbus.com/PdfUploads/Timetable_42347_%20Cambridge%20citi%207.pdf">Citi 7</a> towards Cambridge, or
    <a href="http://www.stagecoachbus.com/PdfUploads/Timetable_42110_Cambridge%20citi%208.pdf">Citi 8</a> towards Cottenham).
    You will need to get off the bus at Drummer Street bus station and <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/YCr8E">walk to the venue</a> (approx. 20 mins).
</p>

